        <H1>Penguins</H1>
        <p> Penguins are a group of flightless seabirds,
             primarily found in the Southern Hemisphere,
              that are highly adapted for life in the water. 
              They are known for their black and white
               plumage, flippers (modified wings), 
            and streamlined bodies,
             which make them excellent swimmers and divers. 
             Most penguins spend a s
             ignificant portion of their lives in the 
             ocean, hunting for fish, krill, and squid. </p>
             <hr>
             <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTXS25ZWAzx2p8f_bseBWZ0EyCpDLookSrP-Q&s">
