             <h1>Facts</h1>
             <ol>
                <li>penguins don't have teeth, but instead have spines in their mouths to help swallow prey.</li>
                <br>
                <li>unique adaptations for survival in cold climates, including specialized feathers and the ability to drink salt water.</li>
             <br>
             <br>
             <li>undergo a "catastrophic molt," losing all their feathers at once. Furthermore, while many penguins are monogamous for a season, some species form lifelong bonds. 
            </li>
            <li>Emperor penguins, in particular, are impressive divers, capable of reaching depths of over 1,850 feet and holding their breath for up to 20 minutes</li>
            </ol>
